               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370612-name-994" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370612-name-994" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370612-name-994" type="surname" value="WILBY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370612-name-994" type="given" value="WILLIAM AUGUSTUS"></interp>WILLIAM AUGUSTUS WILBY</persName>
                  </hi>. I lost a shirt on the 12th of April—this is it—the prisoner lived with the Abbe de Rouffigny as servant—I lodged there—he was my wife's uncle and guardian.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370612-name-995" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370612-name-995" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370612-name-995" type="surname" value="WILBY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370612-name-995" type="given" value="ELOISE"></interp>ELOISE WILBY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the wife of William Augustus Wilby. I live at my uncle's house, No. 1, Great Russell-street, Bloomsbury—the prisoner was there as servant of all work—she left without notice—I missed a pair of sugar tongs and some other articles, the property of my uncle—these are his sheets and decanter.</p>
               <p>
